  "response": "Sulfuric acid (H2SO4) is not an element, but a chemical compound. It is composed of two hydrogen atoms, one sulfur atom, and four oxygen atoms. It is a strong, highly corrosive mineral acid that is widely used in industrial processes, such as:\n\n1. Fertilizer production\n2. Petroleum refining\n3. Wastewater processing\n4. Chemical manufacturing\n5. Battery production\n\nThe key characteristics of sulfuric acid include:\n- Colorless to slightly yellow liquid\n- Extremely corrosive\n- High reactivity\n- Dense and viscous\n- Strong oxidizing agent\n\nThe elements involved in sulfuric acid are hydrogen (H), sulfur (S), and oxygen (O), but the compound itself is not an element.",
